{"item_id": "hi19", "provider": "groq", "model": "openai/gpt-oss-20b", "model_key": "groq:openai/gpt-oss-20b", "source_text": "This Windows update is total jugaad: AI everywhere, control nowhere.", "translation": "यह Windows अपडेट पूरी तरह का जुगाड़ है: AI हर जगह, नियंत्रण कहीं नहीं।", "reference_translation": "यह Windows अपडेट पूरा जुगाड़ है: हर जगह एआई है, लेकिन नियंत्रण कहीं नहीं है।", "tags": ["code_mixed_hinglish", "technology_terms", "sarcasm"], "raw_response": {"id": "chatcmpl-10373142-cfd3-4cc1-916c-05a085d11592", "object": "chat.completion", "created": 1777328500, "model": "openai/gpt-oss-20b", "choices": [{"index": 0, "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": "यह Windows अपडेट पूरी तरह का जुगाड़ है: AI हर जगह, नियंत्रण कहीं नहीं।", "reasoning": "We need to translate the Reddit text into natural Hindi written in Devanagari. Preserve product names, company names, person names, subreddit names, and Reddit abbreviations such as AITA or NTA. Keep tone and slang, but no explanations. Return only the Hindi translation.\n\nThe text: \"This Windows update is total jugaad: AI everywhere, control nowhere.\"\n\nWe need to translate into Hindi, natural, Devanagari. Keep product names: Windows. Keep slang: \"total jugaad\" is already Hindi slang. \"AI everywhere, control nowhere.\" So translation: \"यह Windows अपडेट पूरी तरह का जुगाड़ है: AI हर जगह, नियंत्रण कहीं नहीं।\" But we need to preserve product names: Windows. Keep tone and slang. So maybe: \"यह Windows अपडेट पूरी तरह का जुगाड़ है: AI हर जगह, नियंत्रण कहीं नहीं।\" That seems fine. Use Devanagari. Return only translation."}, "logprobs": null, "finish_reason": "stop"}], "usage": {"queue_time": 0.048617451, "prompt_tokens": 166, "prompt_time": 0.008315238, "completion_tokens": 221, "completion_time": 0.234940077, "total_tokens": 387, "total_time": 0.243255315, "completion_tokens_details": {"reasoning_tokens": 193}}, "usage_breakdown": null, "system_fingerprint": "fp_deb540145b", "x_groq": {"id": "req_01kq8ghbf6fv